Where can VLAs be declared?	<b>Block scope only</b>. Cannot be static, extern, or at file scope. Size determined at declaration.
What is sizeof for a VLA?	<b>Evaluated at runtime</b>. Unlike regular arrays where sizeof is compile-time constant.<br><pre><code>int n = 10;
int arr[n];
