int arr[n] = {0};  // ERROR: cannot initialize VLA</code></pre>
What is a variably modified type?	Any type that depends on a VLA, including pointers to VLAs.<br><pre><code>int n = 10;
int (*p)[n];  // pointer to VLA</code></pre>

# === SECTION 5: Designated Initializers ===
What are designated initializers in C99?	<b>Initialize specific elements</b> by index or member name.<br><pre><code>int arr[10] = {[5] = 50, [8] = 80};
struct point p = {.y = 20, .x = 10};</code></pre>
How do designated initializers work for arrays?	<pre><code>int arr[5] = {
    [0] = 10,
    [2] = 30,
    [4] = 50
