How do designated initializers work for structs?	<pre><code>struct point { int x, y, z; };
struct point p = {
    .z = 30,
    .x = 10
    // .y defaults to 0
};</code></pre>
Can you mix designated and positional initializers?	<b>Yes</b>. Positional values continue after designated ones.<br><pre><code>int arr[] = {[2] = 20, 21, 22};
// arr = {0, 0, 20, 21, 22}</code></pre>

