What is a compound literal in C99?	An <b>unnamed object</b> created with type and initializer list. Has automatic storage duration in block scope.<br><pre><code>(int[]){1, 2, 3}
(struct point){.x = 10, .y = 20}</code></pre>
How do you use compound literals?	<pre><code>// Pass struct to function without variable:
